Step 1. Calculate Debt to Equity Ratio  
• From the balance sheet, Total Owner’s Equity is 16,112,375.10 and Total Liabilities is obtained by subtracting Owner’s Equity from Total Liabilities and Owner’s Equity.  
  Total Liabilities = 23,717,525.01 – 16,112,375.10 = 7,605,149.91  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner’s Equity = 7,605,149.91 / 16,112,375.10 ≈ 0.47  

Step 2. Calculate Net Profit Margin  
• From the income statement, Net Profit = 112,375.10 and Total Revenue = 775,598.77  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100 ≈ (112,375.10 / 775,598.77) × 100 ≈ 14.48%  

Step 3. Calculate Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio  
• From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -967,147.02  
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = 7,605,149.91  
• Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio = -967,147.02 / 7,605,149.91 ≈ -0.13  

Thus, the solution is:  
{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.47",
    "Net Profit Margin": "14.48%",
    "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "-0.13"
  }
}
